<section class="hero-section">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy rise-in">
        <span class="eyebrow">Personal media manager</span>
        <h1 class="display-title">Stay visible without living online.</h1>
        <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
          Ayla reminds you when it is time to capture something real, asks for the missing photo, video, or context,
          and turns your actual life and work into drafts you can approve.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <%= link_to "Start with Ayla", new_user_registration_path, class: "button-primary" %>
          <%= link_to "See how it works", root_path(anchor: "how-it-works"), class: "button-secondary" %>
        </div>

        <div class="proof-row">
          <span class="proof-chip">Built from your real life</span>
          <span class="proof-chip">Keeps you consistent</span>
          <span class="proof-chip">Feels like a personal media manager</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-stack rise-in" style="animation-delay: 120ms;">
        <div class="surface-panel surface-panel--soft mockup-window">
          <div class="mockup-window__top">
            <span>Ayla assistant thread</span>
            <div class="mockup-window__dots">
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mockup-layout">
            <div class="chat-thread">
              <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--assistant">
                <small>Ayla</small>
                You shipped the onboarding refresh yesterday. Send me the quick screen recording before it disappears into your camera roll.
              </div>

              <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--user">
                <small>You</small>
                Just uploaded a 30-second clip and two screenshots. The big win was reducing drop-off after sign-up.
              </div>

              <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--assistant">
                <small>Ayla</small>
                Perfect. What changed, what problem did it solve, and what did you learn after launching it?
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="capture-column">
              <div class="mini-panel">
                <span class="mini-panel__label">Cadence</span>
                <strong class="mini-panel__title">Ayla keeps the week moving</strong>
                <p>Tuesday reminder, Thursday follow-up, Sunday recap. You stay present without babysitting your feed.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="mini-panel">
                <span class="mini-panel__label">Draft ready</span>
                <strong class="mini-panel__title">LinkedIn post</strong>
                <p>“We rebuilt onboarding because great products still lose people in small moments of friction...”</p>
              </div>

              <div class="mini-panel">
                <span class="mini-panel__label">What it protects</span>
                <strong class="mini-panel__title">Real moments</strong>
                <p>Client wins, product launches, behind-the-scenes progress, and the lessons you would have forgotten by tomorrow.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="surface-panel">
          <span class="eyebrow">The promise</span>
          <p class="quote-line">Don’t let good moments die in your camera roll.</p>
          <p class="section-copy">
            Ayla does not invent a fake version of you. It notices the real moments, asks for what is missing,
            and helps you turn them into a body of work people can actually follow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="audience">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="surface-panel audience-band">
      <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
        <span class="eyebrow">Made for visible people</span>
        <p class="section-copy">
          Founders, creators, freelancers, consultants, and operators building a personal brand without turning publishing into a full-time job.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="audience-tag-grid">
        <span class="audience-tag">Founders</span>
        <span class="audience-tag">Creators</span>
        <span class="audience-tag">Freelancers</span>
        <span class="audience-tag">Consultants</span>
        <span class="audience-tag">Operators</span>
        <span class="audience-tag">Personal brands</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Ayla keeps your presence alive, one real moment at a time.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
        The flow is simple: Ayla notices when you have gone quiet, asks for what matters, and helps you turn lived moments into publishable drafts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-grid">
      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">01</span>
        <h3>Ayla notices the silence.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">It reminds you when it is time to capture something instead of letting another week disappear without documentation.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">02</span>
        <h3>Ayla asks for the raw material.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">A quick video, a screenshot, a photo, a voice note, or a few lines about what happened.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">03</span>
        <h3>Ayla gets the missing context.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">It follows up with the questions a real media manager would ask: what changed, why it mattered, what you learned.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">04</span>
        <h3>Ayla proposes drafts.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">Posts, stories, hooks, or recap angles built from your voice, your work, and your actual lived context.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">05</span>
        <h3>You approve what feels true.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">You stay in control. Nothing goes out unless it sounds like you and reflects something real.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step-card">
        <span class="step-index">06</span>
        <h3>Your presence compounds over time.</h3>
        <p class="section-copy">Ayla helps you sustain consistency so your ideas, launches, and progress stop getting lost between busy weeks.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="difference">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why it feels different</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Most AI tools start with a blank box. Ayla starts with your life.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
        Ayla is not here to fabricate a personality for you. It is here to protect your real moments from being forgotten and to remove the friction between living and publishing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="compare-grid">
      <article class="compare-card">
        <h3>Typical AI content tools</h3>
        <p>Great at generating words. Not great at helping you notice, collect, and hold onto the raw material that makes your voice worth following.</p>

        <div class="compare-list">
          <span>Start with prompts instead of lived moments</span>
          <span>Produce generic outputs that sound interchangeable</span>
          <span>Leave you alone to remember what is worth posting</span>
          <span>Do not build consistency into your week</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="compare-card compare-card--accent">
        <h3>Ayla</h3>
        <p>Acts more like a high-level media manager: it nudges, follows up, organizes, drafts, and keeps your presence tied to something real.</p>

        <div class="compare-list">
          <span>Reminds you when it is time to capture something</span>
          <span>Works from real videos, photos, notes, and context</span>
          <span>Asks the questions that sharpen the story</span>
          <span>Keeps you visible without asking you to live online</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">Who it helps most</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">For people doing real work with a brand attached to their name.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
        Ayla is for the kind of person who has plenty to share, but not the headspace to remember, organize, and publish everything in the moment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="persona-grid">
      <article class="persona-card">
        <h3>Founders</h3>
        <p>Keep your product journey visible while you stay focused on building. Launches, lessons, hard decisions, and wins stop going undocumented.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="persona-card">
        <h3>Creators</h3>
        <p>Turn behind-the-scenes moments, rough thoughts, and daily fragments into a clear publishing rhythm without forcing constant performance.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="persona-card">
        <h3>Freelancers & consultants</h3>
        <p>Capture client insights, process snapshots, and outcome-driven stories before they vanish into Slack threads and memory.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="surface-panel surface-panel--accent quote-panel">
      <span class="eyebrow">The emotional truth</span>
      <p class="quote-line">Most people don’t disappear online because they have nothing to say. They disappear because the moment passes.</p>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
        The product shipped. The client finally said yes. The talk went well. The camera roll filled up. Then the week got busy and the thread died.
        Ayla is built to keep those moments alive long enough to become part of your public body of work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="shell shell--wide">
    <div class="surface-panel cta-panel">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Your personal media manager</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Keep showing up without inventing a fake version of yourself.</h2>
        <p class="section-copy section-copy--lead">
          Ayla reminds you, asks, drafts, and keeps you consistent. Built from your real life, not generated from nothing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-actions">
        <%= link_to "Create your account", new_user_registration_path, class: "button-primary" %>
        <%= link_to "Sign in", new_user_session_path, class: "button-secondary" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
